parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, and experience intermittent warning lights, which can lead to accidents, increased risk of injury, and decreased vehicle safety.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls
loses power
warning lights on the instrument panel illuminate intermittently
headlights flicker on and off
dashboard lights go out
and the vehicle goes into neutral or first gear on its own.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, and experience electrical system failures, which can lead to accidents, increased risk of injury, and decreased vehicle safety.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls
loses power
warning lights on the instrument panel illuminate intermittently
headlights flicker on and off
and the dashboard lights go out.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electronic shift module can cause the vehicle to go into neutral or first gear on its own, which can lead to accidents, increased risk of injury, and decreased vehicle safety.
symptoms: The vehicle goes into neutral or first gear on its own
warning lights on the instrument panel illuminate intermittently
and the vehicle experiences loss of power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the interior door handles can cause passengers to become trapped inside the vehicle in emergency situations, leading to potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Cracked or broken interior door handles
inability to open doors from the inside
inoperable door handles.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission control system can cause the vehicle to unexpectedly accelerate, lose power, or become stuck in gear, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates rapidly without input from the driver
the vehicle loses power
the vehicle becomes stuck in gear
the lights on the dashboard illuminate
the engine revs up on its own
the vehicle jerks or lunges while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electronic shift module can cause the vehicle to shift into neutral or first gear on its own, leading to loss of control and accidents.
symptoms: The lights around the PND21 circle all the gears
the vehicle shifts into neutral or first gear on its own
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to lose power, experience electrical surges, and lose critical systems such as power steering and ABS brakes, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The dashboard lights illuminate
the gas gauge fluctuates
the headlights turn off
the power steering and ABS brakes fail
the vehicle experiences electrical surges.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Loss of Engine Power and Assisted Systems
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden loss of engine power, power steering, and brake assistance can increase the risk of a crash, especially when driving on city roads or highways, and can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The engine loses power
the power steering system fails
the brakes seem to not work or are difficult to operate
the vehicle becomes difficult to control.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Manufacturer's Failure to Address Known Safety Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The manufacturer's failure to address known safety issues can lead to continued risk of accidents, injuries, or fatalities, as well as erosion of trust in the brand and the automotive industry as a whole.
symptoms: Vehicle owners receive recall notices but no repair or replacement parts are available
manufacturers fail to provide timely solutions to known safety issues
vehicle owners are left with unsafe vehicles.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Defective Passenger Side Air Bag Warning Indicator
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The continuous illumination of the passenger side air bag warning indicator can distract the driver, increase the risk of an accident, and potentially lead to injury or death in the event of a crash.
symptoms: The passenger side air bag warning indicator remains illuminated
the air bag warning light is continuously on.
